    "intro": "Interpretation moves from what the text says to what the author means — discerning Daniel's theological intent in his first-century Babylonian context and tracing how that intent connects to the larger canonical story. The five movements below follow the chapter's argument from the sovereign giving of 1:2 through the empirical vindication of 1:15 to the enduring ministry of 1:21. Greek lexical notes are replaced with Hebrew notes where relevant, since Daniel 1 is composed in Hebrew.",
